To find the superset of set A and B by taking their union, we combine all the elements from both sets without repeating any elements. 

The union of sets A and B is denoted as A ∪ B.

A = {1, 2, 3}
B = {3, 4, 5}

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}

So, the superset of set A and B by taking their union is {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}.
